The paper discusses the use of spiking neural networks for pattern recognition problems, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The proposed device is a spintronic synapse, which involves the use of electronic and magnetic properties, suggesting that it could also fall under the categories of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). The paper also discusses the interfacing of the spintronic synapses with CMOS neurons and learning circuits, which falls under the categories of electronic devices and circuits (cs.EL) and architecture (cs.AR).
